                  <provenance>Illuminated by at least three artists who worked in Pisa in the mid- and later 14th century; these leaves probably come from at least three different sets of volumes. Two leaves in the Wallace Collection, London, may come from the same manuscripts.</provenance>
                  <provenance>Later pagination is like that of manuscripts from S. Niccolò, Pisa.</provenance>
                  <provenance>Several of the leaves have numbers and prices inscribed in 19th-century pencil, suggesting that they were being offered for sale individually, before being bound.</provenance>
                  <provenance>
                     <persName key="person_477" role="fmo"><!-- not found in VIAF -->Harry Greenwood Butterfield</persName>, given to him by a patient in lieu of payment of fees.</provenance>
                  <acquisition when="1976">Placed on deposit at the Bodleian in 1976 by Butterfield's daughter, <persName key="person_887" role="dnr"><!-- not found in VIAF -->Mrs. E. Saint, of Headington, Oxford</persName>, and kept under the shelfmark as Dep. a. 52; given to the Library through the Friends of the Bodleian in 1997, and re-referenced as MS. Don. a. 11.</acquisition>
